[[File:John 3.16 in Georgian (Dowling, 1912).JPG|thumb|Gospel of John 3.16 in Georgian]]
The Bible was first translated into the [[Georgian language]] as early as the 5th century.<ref>Philip A. Noss ''A history of Bible translation'' 2007 2.4. Georgian translation By the second half of the fifth</ref> The [[Vani Gospels]] (Vani Four Gospels; Georgian: ვანის ოთხთავი, ''Vanis otkhtavi'') is an illuminated manuscript of the gospels in the Georgian [[Nuskhuri]] script dating from the end of the 12th–early 13th centuries. Recently a new translation was completed by the [[Institute for Bible Translation]].

