The [[Nawayath]]s speaks a dialect called ‘Nawayathi’. It is an amalgam of [[Persian language|Persian]], [[Arabic]], [[Marathi language|Marathi]] and [[Hindi]], with [[Konkani language|Konkani]] as its base. The Navayath language uses Persian script for writing.  "Persian script" was being used to write by the Nawaytis long before the language Urdu came into existence.

