[[File:Ĉ.png|thumb|Majuscule and minuscule ĉ in [[Doulos SIL]]]]
{| align="right" cellpadding="4" style="border: 1px solid #aaaaaa; margin: 0 0 10px 10px; padding: 10px; font-size: 36pt; line-height: 36pt; text-align: center;"
| Ĉ ĉ
|}
{{Esperanto sidebar |expanded=Language}}

'''Ĉ''' or '''ĉ''' (C [[circumflex]]) is a [[consonant]] in [[Esperanto orthography]], representing the sound {{IPAblink|t͡ʃ}}.

It is based on the letter ''[[c]]''. Esperanto orthography uses a [[diacritic]] for all four of its postalveolar consonants, as do the Latin-based [[Slavic languages|Slavic]] alphabets. Letters and [[Digraph (orthography)|digraph]]s that are similar to ''ĉ'' and represent the same sound include [[Slovenian language|Slovene]] ''č,'' [[Polish language|Polish]] digraph ''cz'', [[English language|English]] and [[Spanish language|Spanish]] digraph ''ch,'' [[French language|French]] [[Digraphs and trigraphs|trigraph]] ''tch'', [[Norwegian language|Norwegian]] trigraph ''tsj'', [[German language|German]] [[tetragraph]] ''tsch'', and [[Italian language|Italian]] ''c'' before ''i'' or ''e.''

